description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a personal assistant to the Cancer Business Unit for Cwm Taf Morgannwg UHB; based at the Royal Glamorgan Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide a comprehensive, high quality Personal Assistant service to the Cancer Business Unit . The successful candidate will be working in a rewarding, but challenging working and will have excellent organisational, communication, relationship and people management skills, judgement, diplomacy and ability to work calmly under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must possess a high level of attention to detail and accuracy and an understanding of confidentiality and sensitivity is a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job role is varied and requires individuals who can adapt well, meet deadlines and be able to work in a fast paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keryn Jones - Senior Cancer Manager&lt;/p&gt;
